A@sotaqal~ato\n                      \n                     \n                        wasuhayolN A_i*aA A@sotaqal~a yamaAniY"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "O thou marrier of Eth-Thureiyà to Suheyl, by thine acknowledgment of the everlasting existence of God,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(or, as it sometimes means,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I ask God to prolong thy life,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ") tell me,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "how can they meet together? She is of the northern region when she rises, and Suheyl, when he rises, is of the southern region"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Har p. 276. [But I have substituted"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A@ll~`ha", "text_ar": "ا@للّٰهَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "All~`hu", "text_ar": "اللّٰهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yamaAniY", "text_ar": "يَمَانِى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yamaAnK", "text_ar": "يَمَانٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". See also the notice of the poet above named in the work of Ibn-Khillikán: (I have the express authority of the TA for thus writing this name:) and De Sacy's Anthol. Gramm. Arabe, p. 139.]) [Freytag states that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qadamaA suhayolK", "text_ar": "قَدَمَا سُهَيْلٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is the name of"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Two stars which are behind Canopus;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "on the authority of Meyd: and also mentions the name of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "shyl Al$Am", "text_ar": "سهيل الشام"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "shyl Alfrd", "text_ar": "سهيل الفرد"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as given to"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Certain stars in the constellation Anguis;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "adding that Canopus is distinguished from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "shyl Al$Am", "text_ar": "سهيل الشام"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "by the name of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "shyl Alymn", "text_ar": "سهيل اليمن"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".] The name of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^uxotaAsuhayolK", "text_ar": "اُخْتَاسُهَيْلٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The two sisters of Canopus"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] is applied to"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al$~iEoraY", "text_ar": "الشِّعْرَى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlEabuwru", "text_ar": "العَبُورُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Sirius"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al$~iEoraY AlgumayoSaA='u", "text_ar": "الشِّعْرَى الغُمَيْصَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Procyon"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "],"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "together."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S and K in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$Er", "text_ar": "شعر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) [See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaDaAri", "text_ar": "حَضَارِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alwazonu", "text_ar": "الوَزْنُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]"}], "source_refs": ["TA", "Lth"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}